sentences: Fredrikke Amalie Holtemann Rynning Waaler (7 May 1865 â€“ 2 February 1952) was a Norwegian composer, violinist, and proponent for women's rights.
Waaler was born in Eidsvoll to Paul Emil Rynning and Anne Margrethe Holtermann.
Waaler played first violin in the Oslo Musikforening orchestra in 1885.
She founded and led the first orchestra in Hamar in 1893, while also conducting a choir there.
